The paper deals with the query complexity of testing properties defined by read-once formulas, which is a topic in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and data structures for testing and estimation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of information theory and probability theory in the analysis of the query complexity, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper deals with testing and approximation of properties, which could make it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Finally, the paper involves the study of combinatorial structures and their properties, which could make it relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
